  "description": {
   "en": "A red hibiscus tops the fence so tall,\nPassersby greet but leave without a call.\nThis humble flower, unworthy of a vase,\nWould lose its glow by morning’s soft embrace.\n \nSummer's breezes whisper by,\nHesitant they float and shy.\nCarrying forest scents anew,\nWhile hibiscus stays blushing in the dew.\n\nTomorrow, when the winds return,\nThe hibiscus longs for sweet scents to burn.\nA flower with just beauty's grace,\nLacks a fragrance to embrace.\n \nWinds, aware of this design,\nBestow the summer’s scent so fine.\nThe hibiscus blooms at dawn’s first light,\nA truth strange, a wonder in sight.\n \nYet fate cannot be denied,\nBlaming winds for love untried.\nWithout waiting for the day to break,\nA silent farewell, hard to forsake.\n \nWinds wander, searching for a face,\nIs it the one who lost the race?\n...\n\nBach Tu Chi is a young master from the wealthy Bach family. Despite being only 17 years old, he suffers from severe tuberculosis and faces a challenging family situation, having grown up without his father's love and experiencing conflicts with his relatives. Fortunately, he meets Luu Trac Vu, an orphaned boy who roams the streets. Bach Tu Chi takes him in to be his close servant. Since bringing Trac Vu home, Bach Tu Chi has developed a fondness for this servant..."
  },
